[src:calculus-of-variations-deep/calculus-of-variations] Recently, methods have been developed to incorporate symmetry information directly into the inverse problem of the calculus of variations.
[src:calculus-of-variations-deep/calculus-of-variations] By combining the Helmholtz conditions involved in the inverse problem with relations derived from Noether's identity, it is possible to reconstruct Lagrangians that reproduce given equations of motion while ensuring the presence of prescribed symmetries.
